social_posts.post_text:
Well, our four year project, the Tom Egan Memorial Route, is now a pile of boulders underneath Snowpatch Spire. 

The dots barely connected to make it a free climb and I doubt I’ll ever find anything else so on the edge of possibility. 

The line forced us to rise to the challenge and become better climbers, physically and mentally.  A catalyst for change.  I’m grateful for the times spent on that mint slice of perfect granite. 

@senderfilms @reelrock @kyleberkompas @brettlowell 📸
Grateful for friends, family and the outrageous places where we get to play. On to 2023. Happy New Year!

October 2005.  @jason_kruk and I arrived in the early morning at the Heart Ledges on the Salathe Wall.  We recognized the famed pirate @ammonmcneely immediately, winching his bags on the Jolly Roger, a fearsome, seldom-climbed A5. “Good to see some youngsters up here, you guys got it,” encouraged Ammon. 

Things came to a grinding halt a couple pitches higher as I dangerously slithered down the unprotectable Hollow Flake, armed with every piece of gear we collectively owned, showcasing a major lack of wide crack technique. 

By that time it was 11am cocktail hour on Mammoth Terraces for Ammon. Hoisting a King Cobra and the Jolly Roger Flag he yelled pirate jargon for all to hear. “Yarrrr... matey!!!!!”

I saw Ammon many times throughout the next handful of years. Always very friendly and very encouraging. 

Rest In Peace El Cap Pirate.  Big wall legend and wild-man to the max. 

@pictures_of_fidelman 📸🏴‍☠️
‘Twas one of those great days in the Sea to Sky along with the original Finestone Cowboy himself. 🤘🏼To many more! @finestonephoto

The great Mount Colonel Foster before the nighttime waterfall rappels, quick shiver bivy and misguided errant drainage descent. 🤦‍♂️. Beauty place to go climbing! #vancouverislandalps #stratchconaprovincialpark

The list of clinics available is now live for the @arcteryxacademy in Squamish August 24th-27. Check out the link in my profile. 

Scope them now and be ready to pull the trigger when they are up for grabs on July 18 12pm PST. They tend to sell out very quickly. 

Here’s a @johnpricephotography image of @vikkiweldon enjoying those dreamy evening rays high on the Prow Wall. 

Looking forward to the event!

I first came to the Bugs in 2008 with @confluenceclimbinggym aka Chris Brazeau and the place stole my heart. 

So many impressive lines to try.  A true epicentre of alpine granite free climbing. 

The heavy-hitting duo @tommycaldwell and @alexhonnold dropped by on their mega bike journey from Colorado to Alaska. Was a treat to see the dream team in action and take a walk down memory lane. 

Good times my friends! @sonnietrotter @taylor._shaffer @renan_ozturk @snackfarmer @timgmcallister @maurybirdwell @ad_wyatt

A couple weeks ago @sebapelletti @brownie.likethefood and I ventured deep into the heart of the coast range with the help of @whitesaddleair. 

I’d heard tales of the Klattasine for years but was tipped off in earnest when I stumbled upon a piece in the 1987 CAJ. 

We found what we were looking for. Full-value steep rock in a remote setting. 

@arcteryx @dmm_wales @lasportivana @maximropes
On the first ascent of The Lonesome Crowded West, 5.11+, Warbird, Klattasine Range with @sebapelletti. @brownie.likethefood 📸 @arcteryx @lasportivana @maximropes @dmm_wales

social_posts.post_text:
“While perusing the 1988 Canadian Alpine Journal this spring, I was tantalized by the photos of this remote mountain landscape showcasing the kinds of alluring steep white granite walls dreams are made of.

In August, @sebapelletti, @brownie.likethefood, and I ventured deep into the heart of the Coast Mountain Range to the seldom-visited Klattasine Range.

Upon arrival, we discovered that history had not led us astray. The walls - while not gigantic - were of top-notch stone." - @willstanhope

More from 'The Golden Klattasine' in our stories.

📸: @brownie.likethefood #arcteryx

When this photo was taken by @richwheaterphoto circa 2009 I climbed with a feverish intensity that almost seems a bit foreign to me now, though I feel it still at times. 

Days off the rock were kind of tortuous in those days. 

Nowadays the love is still there, but it’s more of a day-in-day-out kind of love. 

@arcteryx asked us to write about what came to mind for the #NoWastedDays campaign.  For me, it’s the ebbs and flows of passion.

Delightful trip to the Utah desert getting pumped silly and dabbling a bit on Hayden Kennedy’s Indian Creek masterpiece, The Kokanee Corner. A king line if there ever was one. I’ll be back. 

Also added a bolt to my route Down In Albion, replacing the aging knife blades HK whaled in circa 2012. Still a spicy lead though, and take care if you attempt. 

Thanks for lending me the drill @pkingsbury !  Check out Pat’s new company @arizona_mountaineering_gear. Nifty bungees for top rope soloing and more to come.
